      <outline text="BITE-SIZE #wfe-ignore-item ">
        <outline text="The Goals of Computer Security #slide #CI7100 #CI7160-intro #CI7130_Intro #basic #CI6280 ">
          <outline text="We will define as the main goals (or requirements) of Computer Security (“CIA”):">
            <outline text="Confidentiality" />
            <outline text="Integrity" />
            <outline text="Availability" />
          </outline>
          <outline text="This terminology is adopted by academia and industry" />
          <outline text="Note: cannot “guarantee” absolute security" />
        </outline>
        <outline text="Threats, Vulnerabilities and Controls #slide #CI7100 #CI7160-intro #CI7130_Intro #basic #CI6280 ">
          <outline text="&lt;i&gt;Threat&lt;/i&gt;: set of circumstances with potential to exploit vulnerability and create a risk of harm" />
          <outline text="&lt;i&gt;Vulnerability&lt;/i&gt;: potentially exploitable weakness of an asset" />
          <outline text="&lt;i&gt;Attack&lt;/i&gt;: realisation of a threat (&quot;threat event&quot;)" />
          <outline text="&lt;i&gt;Risk&lt;/i&gt;: occurs if “matching” threat and vulnerability exist" />
          <outline text="&lt;i&gt;Control&lt;/i&gt;: a mitigation technique, either eliminate the threat and/or close the vulnerability" />
        </outline>
        <outline text="Basic Security Methodology #slide #CI6240_SM-1 #CI7100 #CI7160_D1 #CI7130_Intro #basic #CI6280 ">
          <outline text="The basic methodology in computer security is:">
            <outline text="We detect uncovered vulnerabilities in our system" />
            <outline text="We think about potential threats to our system" />
            <outline text="Finally, we consider available controls (countermeasures)" />
          </outline>
          <outline text="Impossible to guarantee security, can only minimise risk" />
          <outline text="Need for periodic review" />
        </outline>
      </outline>
